<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,402,1003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,798,823]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Agassiz in L. Agassiz &amp; Desor" authorityYear="1846" box="[323,453,798,823]" class="Echinoidea" family="Temnopleuridae" genus="Salmacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="virgulata">
<emphasis box="[323,453,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">S. virgulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from others in the genus in having uniformly purplish, unbanded primary spines with whitish bases (
<figureCitation box="[546,615,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1964,1986]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,193,1947]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[177,1413,193,1947]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Test features and spines of Salmacis virgulata (WUSL/ER/89): A, aboral view; B, oral view; C, ambital ambulacrum; D, ambital interambulacrum; E, ambital spines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2605948/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,402,1003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">
This was the first echinoid species recorded to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[835,946,870,895]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Agassiz, L. &amp; Desor, P. J. E." box="[991,1270,870,895]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" pagination="305 - 374" refId="ref7877" refString="Agassiz, L. &amp; Desor, P. J. E. (1846) Catalogue raisonne des familles, des genres, et des especes de la classe des echinodermes. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, Troisieme Serie, Zoologie, 6, 305 - 374." type="journal article" year="1846">Agassiz &amp; Desor (1846)</bibRefCitation>
, who cited the locality as “ 
<collectingCountry box="[289,372,906,931]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Ceylan</collectingCountry>
” (
<collectingCountry box="[400,516,906,931]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
) for “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Agassiz in L. Agassiz &amp; Desor" authorityYear="1846" box="[588,812,906,931]" class="Echinoidea" family="Temnopleuridae" genus="Salmacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="virgulatus">
<emphasis box="[588,812,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Salmacis virgulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, an incorrect formulation of the name. The 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,906,931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
(EcEh 5940) is from 
<collectingCountry box="[392,506,942,967]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, and is housed at the Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, 
<collectingCountry box="[1205,1281,943,966]" name="France" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vadon, C. &amp; de Ridder, C. &amp; Guille, A. &amp; Jangoux, M." pageId="8" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref11308" refString="Vadon, C., de Ridder, C., Guille, A. &amp; Jangoux, M. (1984) Les types d'Echinides actuels (Echinodermes) du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle de Paris. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 4 e serie, Section A (Zoologie, Biologie et Ecologie animales), 6, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1984">
Vadon 
<emphasis box="[1379,1436,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
1984
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
